{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, you God to whom vengeance belongs, you God to whom vengeance belongs, shine out."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Rise up, you judge of the earth. Pay back the proud what they deserve."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, how long will the wicked, how long will the wicked triumph?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They pour out arrogant words. All the evildoers boast."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They break your people in pieces, Yahweh, and afflict your heritage."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They kill the widow and the alien, and murder the fatherless."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They say, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Yah will not see, neither will Jacob’s God consider.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Consider, you senseless among the people; you fools, when will you be wise?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He who implanted the ear, won’t he hear? He who formed the eye, won’t he see?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He who disciplines the nations, won’t he punish? He who teaches man knows."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh knows the thoughts of man, that they are futile."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed is the man whom you discipline, Yah, and teach out of your law,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "that you may give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit is dug for the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For Yahweh won’t reject his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For judgment will return to righteousness. All the upright in heart shall follow it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Who will rise up for me against the wicked? Who will st and up for me against the evildoers?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Unless Yahweh had been my help, my soul would have soon lived in silence."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When I said, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "My foot is slipping!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your loving kindness, Yahweh, held me up."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "In the multitude of my thoughts within me, your comforts delight my soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Shall the throne of wickedness have fellowship with you, which brings about mischief by statute?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They gather themselves together against the soul of the righteous, and condemn the innocent blood."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But Yahweh has been my high tower, my God, the rock of my refuge."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has brought on them their own iniquity, and will cut them off in their own wickedness."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, our God, will cut them off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}